## Description
The **Transform Files (DT) **task allows to process input data using the Doxee Platform 2 Data Transformation software service.

## Configuration
![](data:image/png;base64,)

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- In the **Alias **field, enter the name of the task that will be displayed in the workflow.

- Click on the **Project &gt; Resource **field and select the Data Transformation resource to use.

> Note

For more information, see:

[Data Transformation Program Resource Reference](/doxee-platform/docs/data-transformation-program-resource-reference)

- [Data Transformation Project Resource Reference](/doxee-platform/docs/data-transformation-project-resource-reference)

> Tip

If you select a Data Transformation Project resource, click **Preset **to automatically import the Reader and Writer configuration from the DT project metada. The Writer's output filename will not be imported.

![](data:image/png;base64,) The endpoint used to access the Data Transformation service is: *&lt;site endpoint&gt;/&lt;portal path&gt;/dt/&lt;operation path&gt;*.

- *(optional) *In the **Attributes **field, you may add up to 10 custom attributes to be added to the generated output file:

**{{Account name}}**

- **{{Account alias}}**

- **{{Input filename}}**

- **{{Job name}}**

- **{{Job number}}**

- **{{Job scope}}**

- **{{Step name}}**

- **{{Step alias}}**

- **{{Task name}}**

- **{{Tenant name}}**

- **{{Tenant alias}}**

- **{{Tenant stage}}**

> Note

In addition to system attributes, it is also possible to enter a constant as a custom attribute.

Custom parameters configured during the **Create job **action in the Batch Jobs portal may also be used as custom attributes (see [Doxee Platform Batch Jobs - Managing Jobs](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-batch-jobs-managing-jobs)).

> Important

After adding 10 custom attributes, you cannot add any more unless you delete one of the configured attributes.

- In the **Flags **field, select the execution options:

**Relaxed**: Skip the notification of some errors.

- **Debug**: Log all errors and include detailed information on the errors, specifically errors that occur during execution of the Data Mapper.

- **Legacy**: Use the legacy Data Mangler (retro-compatibility mode).

- *(optional) *Enable **Analytics **tracking.

- *(optional) *To add an **Input Reader**, click  ![](data:image/png;base64,) (**Add**) and fill in the required fields.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

Enter the **Name **of the reader.

> Important

This field is case sensitive.

- Specify the **Disposition **of the input file:

**Single file**: Only one file is expected in the input

> Important

If the input contains more than one file, the task will fail.

- **Multiple files**: Multiple files are expected in the input

> Note

All files will be taken as input for one execution of the task.

- Select the **Format **of the input file. The available options are:

**FLAT**

- **LINE**

- **XML**

- **AFP**

- **PDF**

- **LEA**

- **EI**

- **PEPPOL**

- *(optional) *Enter the filename **Pattern **to filter the files to use (for example: *.csv).

- Select the **Separator **used in the input file. The available options are:

**LF**

- **CR**

- **CRLF**

- Select the required file **Encoding **from the drop-down menu (default value: UTF-8).

- *(optional) *To add an **Input Catalog**, click  ![](data:image/png;base64,) (**Add**) and select one of the available options:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

> Important

The catalog must be in CSV format.

**Resource**: load a catalog as a dependency, selecting an [Asset](/doxee-platform/docs/asset-resource-reference) resource.![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

Enter the **Name **of the catalog.

> Important

This field is case sensitive.

- Select the Asset **Resource **to use for the catalog.

> Note

For more information, see: [Asset Resource Reference](/doxee-platform/docs/asset-resource-reference).

- Enable the **Optional **toggle to indicate that the catalog is optional.

- **Component**: retrieve a catalog from the previous task in the workflow.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

Enter the **Name **of the catalog.

> Important

This field is case sensitive.

- Select the **Source **task.

- Enter a filename **Pattern **to identify the catalog to be retrieved.

> Note

You may provide the exact name of the catalog file, or define a filename pattern to dynamically select the catalog file(s).

- Enable the **Optional **toggle to indicate that the catalog is optional.

- *(optional) *To add an **Output Writer**, click ![](data:image/png;base64,) (**Add**) and fill in the required fields.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

Enter the **Name **of the writer.

> Important

This field is case sensitive.

- Select the **Format **of the output file. The available options are:

**FLAT**

- **XML**

- **EI**

- Enter the **Filename **to use for the output file.

> Note

You may use the following placeholders to insert the value of a custom attribute in the output filename:

**Placeholder**

**Description**

**Example value**

**{{account. name}}**

Unique ID of the account

Tip

You can find it in the DP3 URL once you have selected an account.

account.xxxxxx

**{{account. alias}}**

Alias of the account

> Tip

It is displayed in the top-right corner of the Repository service's UI.

doxee-test

**{{input. filename}}**

Name of the input file

input_TR-1398.zip

**{{job.name}}**

Unique job ID

> Tip

You can find it in the DP3 URL when inspecting the job in the Batch Jobs service UI.

job.xxxxxx

**{{job. number}}**

Unique job number

10000000

**{{job.scope}}**

Stage of the tenant on which the job is executed The possible values are:

production

- test

test

**{{step. number}}**

Unique step ID

step.xxxxxx

**{{step.alias}}**

Unique step number

10000001

**{{task. number}}**

Name of the task

Document Composition task 1

**{{tenant. name}}**

Unique ID of the tenant

> Tip

You can find it in the DP3 URL when working in the Batch Jobs service UI.

tenant.tenant04-prod

**{{tenant. alias}}**

Alias of the tenant

> Tip

It is displayed in the top-right corner of the Batch Jobs service's UI.

EU Central Production

**{{tenant. stage}}**

Stage of the tenant on which the job is executed The possible values are:

- PRODUCTION

- INTEGRATION

INTEGRATION

If you are using the **Split **option, you may use a file pattern rule to construct incremental filenames; for example:

`output_|03:1|.xml`In this example, "03" is the number of digits to use and "1" is the number to start from. The generated output files will be: *o utput_001.xml*, *output_002.xml*, etc.

- *(optional) *Enable the **Split **option to split the output file.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

Select the **Criterion **to use when splitting the output file:

**Documents**: based on the number of documents

- **Size**: based on the file size (in Bytes)

- In the **Limit **field, enter the value to use for the selected criterion

- Select the required file **Encoding **from the drop-down menu (default value: UTF-8).

- In the **Discards Filename **field, enter the name of the discard file to be generated (default value: "discard").

> Note

The **Transform (DP2) **task's output may be connected by the following branch types:

**Branch type**

**Mandatory**

**Description**

**Writer**

X

Indicates the action to perform on output files generated by the selected output writer.

**Discard**

Indicates the action to perform on any discarded outputs.

**All files**

Indicates the action to perform on all files generated by all writers.

> Note

The files will be passed on to the following task in the application chain organized in folders, one for each configured DT Writer.
